RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STREET ART was hustled out early, was encouraged to stay forwardly placed, shuffled back a bit into a stalking position, saved ground and raced on the fence, shifted out at the quarter pole, was four wide and driving down the stretch, caught the early leaders in deep stretch, was encouraged and cleared those two rivals as he drew away for the win. AUX ARCS was sharp out of the gates, vied for the early lead, shifted down into the three path, matched strides with another foe and raced in a set, set the fractions and showed the way as a pair, battled past the quarter, eighth and the sixteenth poles, were cleared by an outside closer within the last few strides, kept on with the momentum of the horse who passed on the outside and ended with second place honors today. GOODNIGHT ARCHIE vied for the early lead, raced along the rail, was joined by another rival and co led, setting the fractions in a set, continued a set into the stretch, matched strides and battled into deep stretch, the pair was cleared by the eventual winner, battled a few more strides with the same foe he had been battling and just came up short, settling for third today. ALL OF US was between rivals early angled over towards the rail while taking back a bit out of traffic, settled along the rail, raced off the pace, was in contention at the five sixteenth pole, drifted wide, raced seven wide in the stretch and closed passing tired rivals. MARKETBOOK was forwardly placed early, raced in the two path while in between foes, stayed in the second tier beside another foe tucked in behind the early leaders, found room in the stretch but had no late kick. PREMIUM vied for the early lead, raced six wide while stalking the leaders, was encouraged and driven, was wide into the stretch and flattened out.. DRIVER showed little. NEVER OVER ME was never involved.
